cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the engineering design of robotic grippers and their optimization towards robust grasping. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper adopts a learning-based method as the baseline to benchmark the effectiveness of each design configuration. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another likely category as the paper uses objects from the YCB dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision research. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the optimal arrangement of the fingers towards robust grasping, which can be seen as an AI optimization problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the influence of the frictional surface on the finger to improve the grasp robustness, which can be seen as a control problem.
